        "pension_ex2": "<strong>Total salary 55 million KRW (Global income 45 million KRW) or more:</strong> Credit rate 13.2% â†’ <strong>1,188,000 KRW refund</strong>",

        "pension_h5": "5. Detailed Guide on Early Termination and Withdrawal",
        "pension_wd_desc": "Since pension accounts are long-term products, you should carefully check the conditions when finding money in the middle.",
        "pension_wd1": "<strong>Pension Savings Fund:</strong> Early withdrawal is relatively free. You can withdraw only a partial amount as needed without terminating the account. However, other income tax of 16.5% is imposed on the principal and operation income that received a tax credit. (Principal that did not receive a tax credit can be withdrawn without tax)",
        "pension_wd2": "<strong>IRP:</strong> In principle, partial withdrawal is impossible. Even if you want to pull only a part because of a sudden need for money, you must terminate the whole account. However, partial withdrawal is exceptionally allowed only when there are special reasons prescribed by law, such as a homelessness person's house purchase, lease deposit, medical treatment for 6 months or more, bankruptcy, etc.",

        "pension_h6": "6. Efficient Investment Strategy",
        "pension_st1": "<strong>Use of TDF (Target Date Fund):</strong> Management becomes easier if you choose a fund that automatically adjusts the ratio of risky and safe assets according to your retirement timing.",
        "pension_st2": "<strong>Dividend ETF Reinvestment:</strong> Dividends generated within the pension account are fully reinvested without tax, so it is the optimal account to hold dividend growth ETFs.",
        "pension_st3": "<strong>Rebalancing:</strong> Regularly check the ratio of assets, sell some profitable assets, and buy assets that have fallen to manage your rate of return.",

        "pension_h7": "7. Precautions when using",
        "pension_nt1": "<strong>Tax Credit Refund Limit:</strong> Tax credit is a system that reduces the tax I have to pay (determined tax). If the determined tax is 0 KRW or less than the credit amount, no additional refund occurs.",
        "pension_nt2": "<strong>Investment Loss Risk:</strong> Investment products such as funds and ETFs have a risk of principal loss.",
        "pension_nt3": "<strong>Pension Receipt Limit:</strong> If the annual receipt amount exceeds 15 million KRW, you must choose global taxation or separate taxation (16.5%), so you should plan your receipt well.",

