        "guide_title": "â„¹ï¸ Site Usage Guide",
        "guide_h1": "\"Investment is ultimately a battle against cost\"",
        "guide_start": "ğŸ’¡ Start of Service: John Bogle's Philosophy",
        "guide_text1": "John Bogle, the founder of the index fund, said. <strong>\"Investment is ultimately a battle against cost.\"</strong><br>For comfortable long-term investment, index funds (ETFs) are the best tool. However, what we tend to overlook is the 'hidden cost'.",
        "guide_why": "ğŸ” Why is this service needed?",
        "guide_text2": "Domestic securities companies and operators do not reveal all the costs involved in operating ETFs in an easy-to-see glance.<br>In order for general investors to know the exact cost, there was a nuisance that they had to download an Excel file from the KOFIA every time, search for unfamiliar standard codes, and contrast the total expense, other expenses, and brokerage/trading fees as of the end of last month one by one.",
        "guide_text3": "We intend to solve this inconvenience. <strong>etfsave.life</strong> automatically collects complex data so that anyone can quickly and easily check the 'real cost' that investors will actually bear.",
        "guide_text4": "This site is a 'self-investment guide' where investors can search for ETFs directly and compare their costs. The provided information is based on objective data, but the final investment judgment must be made through the investor's own careful review.",
        "guide_click_code": "Clicking on the symbol copies the symbol to the clipboard so you can easily search on securities company apps or HTS. Clicking on the name takes you to the corresponding stock details page on Naver Finance. on this stock page, you can check AUM, trading volume, tracking error, etc. mentioned below.",
        "guide_ref": "ğŸ“Š Please refer to it when using",
        "guide_ref_text": "Of course, cost is not everything about a good ETF.",
        "guide_ref1": "<strong>AUM (Asset Under Management Size):</strong> You should check if the fund's size is stable.",
        "guide_ref2": "<strong>Trading Volume:</strong> Liquidity that you can buy and sell whenever you want is important.",
        "guide_ref3": "<strong>Tracking Error:</strong> You should also look at how well it follows the underlying index.",
        "guide_ref_closing": "But for 'installment long-term investors' who steadily collect without selling, cost is one of the most decisive factors determining the rate of return.",
        "guide_cheer": "ğŸŒ± Cheer for your long-term investment",
        "guide_cheer_text": "We hope the data provided by this site will be a small help in protecting your precious assets and making wiser investment decisions.<br>Beyond the barrier of cost, we will walk the path of unwavering long-term investment together.",

        "fomo_title": "ğŸ˜± Psychology Guide for Overcoming FOMO",
        "fomo_intro": "Do not be anxious about others' profit. Investment is a battle with yourself.",
        "fomo_h1": "1. The Reality of the Fear of 'Sudden Poverty'",
        "fomo_text1": "'Sudden poverty' is a neologism started from relative deprivation. When the asset value of others rises and my asset is the same, you feel like you have lost, but this is because the target of comparison was set incorrectly.",
        "fomo_text2": "The purpose of investment should not be to become richer than others, but to <strong>secure the funds necessary for my life cycle safely</strong>. You must keep in mind that others' rate of return is irrelevant to the value of my life.",
        "fomo_h2": "2. What we cannot see: Survivorship bias",
        "fomo_text3": "Success stories exposed to the outside are likely cases of one or two out of tens of thousands. This is called <strong>survivorship bias</strong>.",
        "fomo_case": "<strong>Example: Lottery winner interview</strong><br>We watch interviews of lottery winners on TV and have hope that I can also win. However, millions of losers who failed to win are silent behind it. The investment market is the same. People who lost all their assets due to high-risk investment do not speak out. You must see the possibility of numerous failures hidden behind a single colorful success.",
        "fomo_h3": "3. Risk of Volatility seen through real cases",
        "fomo_risk1": "<strong>Example 1: 2022 LUNA Incident</strong><br>Luna, which was highlighted as an algorithmic stable coin, plunged 99% in value overnight. Assets of hundreds of millions of won converged to 0 won in just a few days, and many investors suffered irreparable damage. It is a representative case showing that unbearable risk of destruction always lurks behind high profit.",
        "fomo_risk2": "<strong>Example 2: Meme Stock Fever</strong><br>Stocks that soared following trends in certain online communities plummeted miserably after a colorful rise. Individual investors who entered at the end of Information catch the top, which results in the loss of long-term investment motivation.",
        "fomo_h4": "4. Guarding against sweet talk and fraud methods",
        "fomo_scam": "Words that you can make big money easily are fraud or dangerous gambling in nine cases out of ten.",
        "fomo_scam1": "<strong>High profit guarantee:</strong> You should suspect words that deterministically guarantee profit that overwhelmingly exceeds the market average rate of return.",
        "fomo_scam2": "<strong>Short-term big break temptation:</strong> Stocks recommended by reading rooms or unverified experts are highly likely to be in a state where stock prices have already risen or are operation stocks.",
        "fomo_h5": "5. How to stay in the market and experience the flow",
        "fomo_stay": "Give up the impatience and stay in the market, which is eventually the way to win.",
        "fomo_stay1": "<strong>Maintaining your own speed:</strong> If others run and you run without preparation, you will fall. Continue saving and investing that fits your income level and fund plan.",
        "fomo_stay2": "<strong>Making time your side:</strong> The magic of compound interest comes from waiting, not impatience. Rather than trying to reverse life in 1-2 years, aim for peace after 10-20 years.",
        "fomo_stay3": "<strong>Experiencing with small amounts:</strong> If investment study is needed, it is important to start with a very small amount that you can afford and experience the physiology of the market yourself.",
        "fomo_concl_title": "Conclusion",
        "fomo_concl": "Investment is not a game of winning over others, but <strong>a game of controlling my own desires</strong>. When you close your ears to the noise of the market and focus on your principles, true asset growth finally begins.",

